OL,3,GNorth East
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FScattered
OL,6,Fshowers fading, with some late
OL,7,Fsunshine and then clear periods
OL,8,Ffollowing. Cloud amounts should
OL,9,Fincrease from the east later in the
OL,10,Fnight, bringing the odd spot of light
OL,11,Frain or drizzle in places. Chilly,
OL,12,Fwith local grass frost.
OL,13,
OL,14,CTuesday:FOn the cloudy side initially,
OL,15,Fhowever intermittent light rain soon
OL,16,Fclearing westwards to leave a mainly
OL,17,Ffine day with some sunshine.
OL,18,FTemperatures near-normal, tempered a
OL,19,Flittle by the onshore breeze.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
